metadata.name: Solitude #176
metadata.description:
Solitude is a study of negative space, contrast and void; made with 6 different particle systems. It's about the loneliness, energy dependency of our species and our interest towards monumental constructions.

------

In 3541, when Solitude was far from its former glory, the high council was assembling; it's now time to find a new way to live. It has been centuries since our people started to harness the power of the stars, but they used every last bit of power to serve as a mass effort to bring people together and strengthen solidarity. But now just a few remain.. With a shortage of manpower and energy, everything decayed so quickly. Now this isolated civilization is built upon the dying stars and waiting for the eternal void. 

It's time for the high council to assemble for one last time to decide what to do next‚Ä¶

metadata.name: Overshadow #35
metadata.description:
As a multitude of shadowy forms rotate around a central point, new lines, shapes, and colors emerge.  An exploration of animation, color, rotation, and opacity.

WARNING: Contains flashing images, extreme in some cases!

Press 's' to save a video.  You can choose between mp4 or gif formats, in a variety of resolutions. The time options are based around seamless points for each individual work.  There are 3 aspects of each work that change over time: Color, Size, and Rotation.  While color and individual options are seamless for that particular aspect, 'Size + Rotation' or 'Full Color + Size + Rotation' will provide the best visually seamless video (note that some works will not have a size option as they don't change in this regard).

p5js, gif.js, h264-mp4-encoder.js

metadata.name: METASYNTAX #123
metadata.description:
Metasyntax is an abstract work on dimensionality.

Syntax is theoretically unidimensional. A syntactic sequence can provide meaning from the interaction between its elements. This sequence is symbolized by a series of shapes piled along a single axis. These shapes can either overlap by themselves, of through their respective spheres of infuence. As such, they collectively project a simple representation of what is at stake with syntactic relationships among lexical agents.

The "meta" aspect is intuitive: this work is an abstract representation of unidimensionality that yields a two-dimensional image computed from a three-dimensional paradigm.

The twist of Metasyntax is hence to be an abstract projection that is quite literally what it is.

metadata.name: Efflorescence #222
metadata.description:
Efflorescence is a piece that bridges between Pouya and Fatima's hand crafted tiles and Gorilla Sun's generative work, and reflects their collective love for patterns and colour. Efflorescence is a generative token that creates unique compositions by random arrangement of different tiles and the colorisation thereof.

This generative token would not have been possible without Zeno Zeng's SVG runtime for P5JS!

Press the down arrow button to export an SVG of the artwork. In live view stroke width can be adjusted by zooming in and out.

metadata.name: CrossWorlds #199
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180¬∞
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.

metadata.name: Crece #87
metadata.description:
¬øCu√°l es la forma de la met√°fora? - What is the shape of the metaphor?


Crece (It grows) is the manifestation of the metaphor in relation to materiality and abstraction.
Only sensations that escape the everyday. The time in which it is built and grows, shows and hides ungraspable instants. In any case: What shape would the metaphor take before it grew or manifested?

This project is based on the investigation of the algorithm used in "99 recorridos" and has to do with three questions, the animated effect of growth of the drawing that resembles roots as in "99 recorridos", but in this case it does not evoke the natural, but the artificial with the inclusion of harsher, straighter lines that is more closely to sci-fi imagery. Second, it has to do with the growth of the algorithm, from new lines of code that give it its personality. Thirdly, a metaphorical, imaginary and internal growth that arises from that dialogue that enriches our souls in this coexistence.

Playing with features:

-Oldness of the metaphor
-Growth impulse of the shape
-Growth duration
-Pigmentary composition of the metaphor
-Rhizome
-Shape of the metaphor
-The moment
